From: Kush Gupta <kugupta@redhat.com>
Subject: [PATCH] sign: fix missing const in payload_decode_cpy

PR #211 missed changing `char *p` to `const char *p` in payload_decode_cpy.
This causes a build failure on GCC 16 (Fedora Rawhide) where strchr()
returns const char* when given const char* input.

Signed-off-by: Kush Gupta <kugupta@redhat.com>
---
 src/lib/sign.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/src/lib/sign.c b/src/lib/sign.c
index 0ba626b..1234567 100644
--- a/src/lib/sign.c
+++ b/src/lib/sign.c
@@ -361,7 +361,7 @@ static struct kv *header_decode (const char *input, const char **endptr)
 static int payload_decode_cpy (const char *input, void **buf, int *bufsz,
                                const char **endptr)
 {
-    char *p;
+    const char *p;
     size_t dstlen;
     void *dst = NULL;
     int saved_errno;

